  "market_context": "USD daily chart from August to October 2023 showing a sustained bullish trend with PD arrays supporting price higher. The analyst uses this chart to demonstrate how trending markets repeatedly reach for previous day highs as a draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "In a bullish trend, price continues to take previous day highs over and over again. Marking each PDH on the daily chart reveals consecutive sweeps, confirming the uptrend and providing a reliable draw on liquidity for entries.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Establish the rule that unless price is consolidating, it will reach for previous day high or previous day low.",
    "Step 2: Open the USD daily chart and observe that PD arrays are supporting price higher, indicating an uptrend.",
    "Step 3: Anticipate price to keep reaching for previous day highs given the bullish structure.",
    "Step 4: Mark out the previous day high and advance one day forward to confirm it was taken.",
    "Step 5: Repeat the process day after day, confirming PDH is swept over and over again.",
    "Step 6: Conclude that this repeated PDH sweep pattern is how to identify a sustained uptrend and define a draw on liquidity for framing entries on lower time frames."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Repeated sweeps of previous day highs define and confirm a bullish trend. Once identified, PDH becomes the easiest and most reliable draw on liquidity, allowing the trader to anticipate targets and frame lower time frame entries with directional bias.",
